  "html": "<h1>Applies to</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>C&#43;&#43;</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h1>What to Check For</h1>\n  <p>Verify that exceptions thrown by input-output functions are handled and error codes are checked.</p>\n  <h1>Why</h1>\n  <p>If errors during file input-output are not handled, unexpected behavior may result leading to a vulnerability.</p>\n  <h1>How to Check</h1>\n  <p>Identify all functions that perform file input-output. Verify that whenever file input-output is performed, code exists that handles possible errors.</p>\n  <h1>How to Fix</h1>\n  <p>Identify all functions that perform file input-output. Identify the possible errors that may result during file IO. Write code that handles exceptions or checks for error codes and responds appropriately.</p>\n  <h1>Additional Resources</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>For more information about handling file IO errors, please see <a href=\"https://www.securecoding.cert.org/confluence/display/cplusplus/FIO33-CPP.&#43;Detect&#43;and&#43;handle&#43;input&#43;output&#43;errors&#43;resulting&#43;in&#43;undefined&#43;behavior\">https://www.securecoding.cert.org/confluence/display/cplusplus/FIO33-CPP.&#43;Detect&#43;and&#43;handle&#43;input&#43;output&#43;errors&#43;resulting&#43;in&#43;undefined&#43;behavior</a></li>\n  </ul>\n  <h1>Related Items</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>\n      <a href=\"/article/e4a3052e-13f2-4062-9a83-49185ff14b0a\">Centralize Error Handling</a>\n    </li>\n  </ul>"
